<item>
            <title>[SOLR-5978] Warning for SOLR-5522 (file/edit) should be removed from example solrconfig.xml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5978</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In /&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5522&quot; title=&quot;Pull modifying the Solr config documents out of Solr 4.x&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5522&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5522&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  the handler configuration code for the admin/fileedit request handler which would o allow modification of Solr Config files was removed from the example solrconfig.xml, but the comments were left in the example file.   New users may be confused by a warning about a possible security vulnerability which actually applies to a handler configuration that was removed from the example.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch coming as soon as I get an issue number&lt;/p&gt;</description>
